{"name":"Grenade","permission":{"default":0,"wypGoDpbSltPFEBU":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"useAbl":"acc","targetNumber":10,"powerPointCost":1,"fatigueTN":10,"dmgType":"wound","dmgSource":"ballistic","nrDice":3,"diceType":"6","extraValue":0,"dmgAbl":"no-abl","minStr":"0","useFocus":"Throwing","weight":0,"cost":"15","quantity":1,"equiped":false,"shortDesc":"","longDesc":"<div title=\"Page 77\">\n<p>Grenades are thrown weapons making use of Accuracy(Throwing) for the attack roll. A grenade attack is typically a <strong>TN 11 Accuracy (Thrown)</strong> test, modified for difficult throws at the GM&rsquo;s discretion</p>\n<p><strong>Range</strong>: Strength*10 meters.</p>\n<p>You can use the Ready action to have the grenade in your hand. You may subsequently take a Ranged Attack action to throw it.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n<div title=\"Page 77\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>Success with a grenade attack means the grenade lands and detonates where you intended. Failure means the grenade lands up to 1d6 meters away in a direction of the GM&rsquo;s choosing, and then explodes.</p>\n<p>Grenades affect everything and everyone within 5 meters of the explosion, dealing damage and any additional effects.</p>\n<p>Action stunts may be used with grenade attacks. Each stunt can affect just one target, and you aren;'t required to allocate all stunts to the same target. If two combatants are in the blast of a grenade and 4 SP were genrated in the attack, then you might use Overcome Toughness on one foe and Knock Prone on the other.</p>\n<p>Unlike attacks with ranged weapons that must be aimed, you don&rsquo;t need to score a direct hit on a target with a grenade or other explosive device, just get close enough to catch them in the blast.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","itemMods":{"itemDamage":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"actorDamage":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"itemActivation":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"focus":{"name":"","value":0,"isActive":false},"defense":{"value":0,"isActive":f